{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PN4TD7umgh8ai9UTmUA3i3","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F15 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC §6.7 — Seed Data (`POST /api/seed`):\n6\t\n7\t- Clears existing data and populates ClickHouse with realistic sample data (BR-102).\n8\t- Idempotent. Should complete in < 30 seconds.\n9\t- 6 event types: `Page Viewed`, `Button Clicked`, `Signup Completed`, `Purchase Completed`, `Subscription Renewed`, `Support Ticket Opened`.\n10\t- 70 users: 50 fully resolved, 10 multi-device, 10 anonymous-only.\n11\t- ~12,000 events over 30 days.\n12\t- Non-uniform distribution: power-law on user activity; `Page Viewed` ~40% of events.\n13\t- String properties: `page`, `button_name`, `plan`, `currency`, `source`.\n14\t- Numeric properties: `amount` (0–500), `duration_seconds` (0–3600), `ticket_count`.\n15\t\n16\tFrom SPEC §6.7 — `GET /api/seed/status`:\n17\t\n18\t- Returns current event count and user count — useful for verifying seed completed.\n19\t\n20\t## Dependencies\n21\t\n22\tCompleted features this builds on:\n23\t- F1 (`features/F1-done.md`) — ClickHouse client singleton (`src/lib/clickhouse.ts`)\n24\t- F2 (`features/F2-done.md`) — Migration script / schema (`scripts/schema.sql`, `scripts/migrate.ts`)\n25\t- F4 (`features/F4-done.md`) — Identity resolution logic (`src/lib/identity.ts`)\n26\t\n27\tFiles that will be imported:\n28\t- `src/lib/clickhouse.ts` — the `clickhouse` singleton client\n29\t- `src/lib/identity.ts` — `resolveIdentityMapping` (or direct insert into `identity_mappings`)\n30\t\n31\t## Files to create or modify\n32\t\n33\t- CREATE `src/lib/seed.ts` — core seed data generation and insertion logic\n34\t- CREATE `src/app/api/seed/route.ts` — `POST /api/seed` handler\n35\t- CREATE `src/app/api/seed/status/route.ts` — `GET /api/seed/status` handler\n36\t- CREATE `src/lib/__tests__/seed.test.ts` — unit tests for seed logic\n37\t\n38\t## Implementation order\n39\t\n40\t1. **Create `src/lib/seed.ts`** — implement the seed data generator:\n41\t   - Define the 6 event types with their property schemas.\n42\t   - Implement a seeded PRNG (`mulberry32`) for reproducible distributions.\n43\t   - Implement power-law user activity distribution (~40% `Page Viewed`).\n44\t   - Generate 70 users: 50 fully resolved (1 device + 1 user_id), 10 multi-device (2–3 devices each + 1 user_id), 10 anonymous-only (device_id only, no user_id).\n45\t   - Generate ~12,000 events distributed over the last 30 days.\n46\t   - Assign appropriate string and numeric properties per event type.\n47\t   - Export a `seedData(client?)` function that:\n48\t     a. Truncates the `events` and `identity_mappings` tables.\n49\t     b. Bulk-inserts generated events via `INSERT ... FORMAT JSONEachRow`.\n50\t     c. Bulk-inserts identity mappings for the 60 resolved users.\n51\t   - Export helper functions for generating users and events (for testability).\n52\t\n53\t2. **Create `src/app/api/seed/route.ts`** — `POST /api/seed`:\n54\t   - Calls `seedData()`.\n55\t   - Returns `201` with `{ ok: true, events: <count>, users: <count> }`.\n56\t   - Returns `500` with `{ error: \"...\" }` on failure.\n57\t\n58\t3. **Create `src/app/api/seed/status/route.ts`** — `GET /api/seed/status`:\n59\t   - Queries ClickHouse for `SELECT count() FROM events` and distinct user count.\n60\t   - Returns `{ events: <number>, users: <number> }`.\n61\t\n62\t4. **Create `src/lib/__tests__/seed.test.ts`** — unit tests for the generation logic (no ClickHouse dependency).\n63\t\n64\t## Sprint contract\n65\t\n66\t- [ ] File `src/lib/seed.ts` exists and exports `seedData`\n67\t- [ ] File `src/app/api/seed/route.ts` exists and exports `POST`\n68\t- [ ] File `src/app/api/seed/status/route.ts` exists and exports `GET`\n69\t- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits with 0 failures\n70\t- [ ] Lint check → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n71\t- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n72\t- [ ] Build check → `pnpm build` exits 0\n73\t\n74\t## Test plan\n75\t\n76\t- **Test file**: `src/lib/__tests__/seed.test.ts`\n77\t- **Module under test**: `src/lib/seed.ts` — user generation, event generation, property assignment, distribution logic\n78\t- **Cases to cover**:\n79\t  - Generates exactly 70 users: 50 fully-resolved, 10 multi-device, 10 anonymous-only\n80\t  - Multi-device users each have 2–3 device IDs\n81\t  - Anonymous-only users have a device_id but no user_id\n82\t  - Generates ~12,000 events (within ±500 tolerance — generation uses randomness)\n83\t  - All 6 event types are present in the generated events\n84\t  - `Page Viewed` events constitute approximately 40% of total (within ±5% tolerance)\n85\t  - Event timestamps span the last 30 days and are within that range\n86\t  - `Purchase Completed` events have numeric `amount` property in range 0–500\n87\t  - `Support Ticket Opened` events have numeric `ticket_count` property\n88\t  - String properties (`page`, `plan`, `currency`, `source`, `button_name`) are present on the relevant event types\n89\t  - `seedData` calls truncate on both tables, then inserts events and identity mappings (mock ClickHouse client)\n90\t  - Identity mappings are created for the 60 non-anonymous users (50 single-device + 10 multi-device with 2–3 devices each)\n91\t- **Integration gap**: `POST /api/seed` HTTP response, `GET /api/seed/status` HTTP response — requires dev server + ClickHouse\n92\t\n93\t## Risks and open questions\n94\t\n95\t- **Truncation safety**: `seedData` truncates both tables before inserting. The spec says \"clears existing data\" and \"idempotent\", so this is correct, but real-world use should be aware data is destroyed.\n96\t- **Power-law distribution**: The spec says \"power-law on user activity\" but doesn't specify the exponent. Will use a Zipf-like distribution where the most active user has ~10× the events of the median user. The test will verify `Page Viewed` is ~40% of total and that event counts per user are non-uniform.\n97\t- **Multi-device identity mappings**: For the 10 multi-device users, each device must be inserted into `identity_mappings` separately. Using direct bulk insert rather than `resolveIdentityMapping` (which does per-row SELECT) for performance.\n98\t- **Event count**: Spec says \"~12,000\" — will target 12,000 exactly but the test will allow ±500 tolerance since the distribution is randomized.\n99\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c72eb9a7-df03-4abb-9f50-785b299289e4","uuid":"620e84b9-bde4-4523-ac28-0436c8cc2d4f","timestamp":"2026-04-15T14:25:38.697Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/features/F15-plan.md","content":"# F15 Plan\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\nFrom SPEC §6.7 — Seed Data (`POST /api/seed`):\n\n- Clears existing data and populates ClickHouse with realistic sample data (BR-102).\n- Idempotent. Should complete in < 30 seconds.\n- 6 event types: `Page Viewed`, `Button Clicked`, `Signup Completed`, `Purchase Completed`, `Subscription Renewed`, `Support Ticket Opened`.\n- 70 users: 50 fully resolved, 10 multi-device, 10 anonymous-only.\n- ~12,000 events over 30 days.\n- Non-uniform distribution: power-law on user activity; `Page Viewed` ~40% of events.\n- String properties: `page`, `button_name`, `plan`, `currency`, `source`.\n- Numeric properties: `amount` (0–500), `duration_seconds` (0–3600), `ticket_count`.\n\nFrom SPEC §6.7 — `GET /api/seed/status`:\n\n- Returns current event count and user count — useful for verifying seed completed.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nCompleted features this builds on:\n- F1 (`features/F1-done.md`) — ClickHouse client singleton (`src/lib/clickhouse.ts`)\n- F2 (`features/F2-done.md`) — Migration script / schema (`scripts/schema.sql`, `scripts/migrate.ts`)\n- F4 (`features/F4-done.md`) — Identity resolution logic (`src/lib/identity.ts`)\n\nFiles that will be imported:\n- `src/lib/clickhouse.ts` — the `clickhouse` singleton client\n- `src/lib/identity.ts` — `resolveIdentityMapping` (or direct insert into `identity_mappings`)\n\n## Files to create or modify\n\n- CREATE `src/lib/seed.ts` — core seed data generation and insertion logic\n- CREATE `src/app/api/seed/route.ts` — `POST /api/seed` handler\n- CREATE `src/app/api/seed/status/route.ts` — `GET /api/seed/status` handler\n- CREATE `src/lib/__tests__/seed.test.ts` — unit tests for seed logic\n\n## Implementation order\n\n1. **Create `src/lib/seed.ts`** — implement the seed data generator:\n   - Define the 6 event types with their property schemas.\n   - Implement a seeded PRNG (`mulberry32`) for reproducible distributions.\n   - Implement power-law user activity distribution (~40% `Page Viewed`).\n   - Generate 70 users: 50 fully resolved (1 device + 1 user_id), 10 multi-device (2–3 devices each + 1 user_id), 10 anonymous-only (device_id only, no user_id).\n   - Generate ~12,000 events distributed over the last 30 days.\n   - Assign appropriate string and numeric properties per event type.\n   - Export a `seedData(client?)` function that:\n     a. Truncates the `events` and `identity_mappings` tables.\n     b. Bulk-inserts generated events via `INSERT ... FORMAT JSONEachRow`.\n     c. Bulk-inserts identity mappings for the 60 resolved users.\n   - Export helper functions for generating users and events (for testability).\n\n2. **Create `src/app/api/seed/route.ts`** — `POST /api/seed`:\n   - Calls `seedData()`.\n   - Returns `201` with `{ ok: true, events: <count>, users: <count> }`.\n   - Returns `500` with `{ error: \"...\" }` on failure.\n\n3. **Create `src/app/api/seed/status/route.ts`** — `GET /api/seed/status`:\n   - Queries ClickHouse for `SELECT count() FROM events` and distinct user count.\n   - Returns `{ events: <number>, users: <number> }`.\n\n4. **Create `src/lib/__tests__/seed.test.ts`** — unit tests for the generation logic (no ClickHouse dependency).\n\n## Sprint contract\n\n- [ ] File `src/lib/seed.ts` exists and exports `seedData`\n- [ ] File `src/app/api/seed/route.ts` exists and exports `POST`\n- [ ] File `src/app/api/seed/status/route.ts` exists and exports `GET`\n- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits with 0 failures\n- [ ] Lint check → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n- [ ] Build check → `pnpm build` exits 0\n\n## Test plan\n\n- **Test file**: `src/lib/__tests__/seed.test.ts`\n- **Module under test**: `src/lib/seed.ts` — user generation, event generation, property assignment, distribution logic\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - Generates exactly 70 users: 50 fully-resolved, 10 multi-device, 10 anonymous-only\n  - Multi-device users each have 2–3 device IDs\n  - Anonymous-only users have a device_id but no user_id\n  - Generates ~12,000 events (within ±500 tolerance — generation uses randomness)\n  - All 6 event types are present in the generated events\n  - `Page Viewed` events constitute approximately 40% of total (within ±5% tolerance)\n  - Event timestamps span the last 30 days and are within that range\n  - `Purchase Completed` events have numeric `amount` property in range 0–500\n  - `Support Ticket Opened` events have numeric `ticket_count` property\n  - String properties (`page`, `plan`, `currency`, `source`, `button_name`) are present on the relevant event types\n  - `seedData` calls truncate on both tables, then inserts events and identity mappings (mock ClickHouse client)\n  - Identity mappings are created for the 60 non-anonymous users (50 single-device + 10 multi-device with 2–3 devices each)\n- **Integration gap**: `POST /api/seed` HTTP response, `GET /api/seed/status` HTTP response — requires dev server + ClickHouse\n\n## Risks and open questions\n\n- **Truncation safety**: `seedData` truncates both tables before inserting. The spec says \"clears existing data\" and \"idempotent\", so this is correct, but real-world use should be aware data is destroyed.\n- **Power-law distribution**: The spec says \"power-law on user activity\" but doesn't specify the exponent. Will use a Zipf-like distribution where the most active user has ~10× the events of the median user. The test will verify `Page Viewed` is ~40% of total and that event counts per user are non-uniform.\n- **Multi-device identity mappings**: For the 10 multi-device users, each device must be inserted into `identity_mappings` separately. Using direct bulk insert rather than `resolveIdentityMapping` (which does per-row SELECT) for performance.\n- **Event count**: Spec says \"~12,000\" — will target 12,000 exactly but the test will allow ±500 tolerance since the distribution is randomized.\n","numLines":99,"startLine":1,"totalLines":99}}}
